16007431Di2015UniqueSeparatorusing System.Text;Di2015NewLineusing System.IO.Ports;Di2015NewLineusing System.Threading;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLinenamespace ConsoleApplication2Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    class ProgramDi2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        static string serialBuffer = "";Di2015NewLine        static string expectedEcho = null;Di2015NewLine        static object expectedEchoLock = new object();Di2015NewLine        static ManualResetEvent expectedEchoReceived = new ManualResetEvent(false);Di2015NewLine        static SerialPort port = new SerialPort("COM1", 19200, Parity.None, 8, StopBits.One);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        static void Main(string[] args)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            port.DataReceived += new SerialDataReceivedEventHandler(port_DataReceived);Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        static void port_DataReceived(object sender, SerialDataReceivedEventArgs e)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            while (port.BytesToRead > 0)Di2015NewLine            {Di2015NewLine                byte[] buffer = new byte[port.BytesToRead];Di2015NewLine                int bytesRead = port.Read(buffer, 0, buffer.Length);Di2015NewLine                if (bytesRead <= 0) return;Di2015NewLine                serialBuffer += Encoding.UTF8.GetString(buffer, 0, bytesRead);Di2015NewLine                string[] lines = serialBuffer.Split('\\r', '\\n');Di2015NewLine                // Don't process the last part, because it's not terminated yetDi2015NewLine                for (int i = 0; i < (lines.Length - 1); i++)Di2015NewLine                {Di2015NewLine                    if (lines[i].Length > 0)Di2015NewLine                        ProcessLine(lines[i]);Di2015NewLine                }Di2015NewLine                serialBuffer = lines[lines.Length - 1]; // keep last partDi2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        static void ProcessLine(string line)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            bool unsolicitedMessageReceived = false;Di2015NewLine            lock (expectedEchoLock)Di2015NewLine            {Di2015NewLine                if (line == expectedEcho)Di2015NewLine                {Di2015NewLine                    expectedEchoReceived.Set();Di2015NewLine                }Di2015NewLine                elseDi2015NewLine                {Di2015NewLine                    unsolicitedMessageReceived = true;Di2015NewLine                }Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLine            if (unsolicitedMessageReceived)Di2015NewLine            {Di2015NewLine               // Process unsolicited/unexpected messagesDi2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        /// <summary>Di2015NewLine        /// Send a command and wait for echoDi2015NewLine        /// </summary>Di2015NewLine        /// <param name="command">The command to send</param>Di2015NewLine        /// <returns>True when echo has been received, false on timeout.</returns>Di2015NewLine        static bool SendCommand(string command)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            lock (expectedEchoLock)Di2015NewLine            {Di2015NewLine                expectedEchoReceived.Reset();Di2015NewLine                expectedEcho = command;Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLine            port.Write(command);Di2015NewLine            return expectedEchoReceived.WaitOne(5000); // timeout after 5 secondsDi2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

16014518Di2015UniqueSeparatorbool IsPdf(string path)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    var pdfString = "%PDF-";Di2015NewLine    var pdfBytes = Encoding.ASCII.GetBytes(pdfString);Di2015NewLine    var len = pdfBytes.Length;Di2015NewLine    var buf = new byte[len];Di2015NewLine    var remaining = len;Di2015NewLine    var pos = 0;Di2015NewLine    using(var f = File.OpenRead(path))Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        while(remaining > 0)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            var amtRead = f.Read(buf, pos, remaining);Di2015NewLine            if(amtRead == 0) return false;Di2015NewLine            remaining -= amtRead;Di2015NewLine            pos += amtRead;Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine    return pdfBytes.SequenceEqual(buf);Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

16023565Di2015UniqueSeparatorpublic static IObserver<T> Switch<T>(this IObservable<IObserver<T>> source)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    var mutex = new object();Di2015NewLine    var current = Observer.Create<T>(x => {});Di2015NewLine    var subscription = source.Subscribe(o =>Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        lock (mutex)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine           current.OnCompleted();Di2015NewLine           current = o;Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    });Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    return Observer.Create<T>(Di2015NewLine        onNext: v =>Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            lock(mutex)Di2015NewLine            {                Di2015NewLine              current.OnNext(v);Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLine        },Di2015NewLine        onCompleted: () =>Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine             subscription.Dispose();Di2015NewLine             lock (mutex)Di2015NewLine             {Di2015NewLine                 current.OnCompleted();Di2015NewLine             }Di2015NewLine        },Di2015NewLine        onError: e =>Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine             subscription.Dispose();Di2015NewLine             lock (mutex)Di2015NewLine             {Di2015NewLine                 current.OnError(e);Di2015NewLine             }Di2015NewLine        });Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

16023792Di2015UniqueSeparatorinternal static List<string> BuildPaths(XmlDocument doc)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    List<string> paths = new List<string>();Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    BuildPaths(doc.DocumentElement, paths);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    return paths;Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLineprivate static void BuildPaths(XmlNode node, List<string> paths, string prefix = "/")Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    if (node.Name == "element")Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        // end case - elements named "element"Di2015NewLine        paths.Add(prefix + node.Attributes["id"].Value);Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine    elseDi2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        // iterate through child nodes that are either not named element or that Di2015NewLine        // have an attribute named "id" (i.e. skip elements named "element" that Di2015NewLine        // lack an id attribute)Di2015NewLine        foreach (XmlNode child in node.SelectNodes("*[not(self::element) or @id]"))Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            BuildPaths(child, paths, prefix + node.Name + "/");Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

16023792Di2015UniqueSeparatorXmlDocument
16023792Di2015UniqueSeparatorprivate static List<string> BuildPaths(XmlNode node, string prefix = "/")Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    // Get child node if current node is the rootDi2015NewLine    if (node.NodeType == XmlNodeType.Document) { node = node.FirstChild; }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    if (node.Name == "element")Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        return new List<string> { prefix + node.Attributes["id"].Value };Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine    elseDi2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        return node.SelectNodes("*[not(self::element) or @id]")Di2015NewLine                   .OfType<XmlNode>()Di2015NewLine                   .Select(n => BuildPaths(n, prefix + node.Name + "/"))Di2015NewLine                   .SelectMany(l => l)Di2015NewLine                   .ToList();Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

16044841Di2015UniqueSeparatorcreate function dbo.F_GREAT_CIRCLE_DISTANCEDi2015NewLine(Di2015NewLine    @Latitude1  float,Di2015NewLine    @Longitude1 float,Di2015NewLine    @Latitude2  float,Di2015NewLine    @Longitude2 floatDi2015NewLine)Di2015NewLinereturns float asDi2015NewLinebeginDi2015NewLine    declare @radius floatDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    declare @lon1  floatDi2015NewLine    declare @lon2  floatDi2015NewLine    declare @lat1  floatDi2015NewLine    declare @lat2  floatDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    declare @a floatDi2015NewLine    declare @distance floatDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    -- Sets average radius of Earth in MilesDi2015NewLine    set @radius = 3956Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    -- Convert degrees to radiansDi2015NewLine    set @lon1 = radians( @Longitude1 )Di2015NewLine    set @lon2 = radians( @Longitude2 )Di2015NewLine    set @lat1 = radians( @Latitude1 )Di2015NewLine    set @lat2 = radians( @Latitude2 )Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    set @a = sqrt(square(sin((@lat2-@lat1)/2.0E)) + (cos(@lat1) * cos(@lat2) * square(sin((@lon2-@lon1)/2.0E))) )Di2015NewLine    set @distance = @radius * ( 2.0E *asin(case when 1.0E < @a then 1.0E else @a end ))Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    return @distanceDi2015NewLineendDi2015NewLine

16050296Di2015UniqueSeparatorpublic WriteableBitmap SaveAsWriteableBitmap(Canvas surface)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    if (surface == null) return null;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    // Save current canvas transformDi2015NewLine    Transform transform = surface.LayoutTransform;Di2015NewLine    // reset current transform (in case it is scaled or rotated)Di2015NewLine    surface.LayoutTransform = null;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    // Get the size of canvasDi2015NewLine    Size size = new Size(surface.ActualWidth, surface.ActualHeight);Di2015NewLine    // Measure and arrange the surfaceDi2015NewLine    // VERY IMPORTANTDi2015NewLine    surface.Measure(size);Di2015NewLine    surface.Arrange(new Rect(size));Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    // Create a render bitmap and push the surface to itDi2015NewLine    RenderTargetBitmap renderBitmap = new RenderTargetBitmap(Di2015NewLine      (int)size.Width, Di2015NewLine      (int)size.Height, Di2015NewLine      96d, Di2015NewLine      96d, Di2015NewLine      PixelFormats.Pbgra32);Di2015NewLine    renderBitmap.Render(surface);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    //Restore previously saved layoutDi2015NewLine    surface.LayoutTransform = transform;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    //create and return a new WriteableBitmap using the RenderTargetBitmapDi2015NewLine    return new WriteableBitmap(renderBitmap);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

16065660Di2015UniqueSeparatorstatic void FindFilenamesInMessage(string message) {Di2015NewLine    // Find all the "letter colon backslash", indicating filenames.Di2015NewLine    var matches = Regex.Matches(message, @"\\w:\\\\", RegexOptions.Compiled);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    // Go backwards. Useful if you need to replace stuff in the messageDi2015NewLine    foreach (var idx in matches.Cast<Match>().Select(m => m.idx).Reverse()) {Di2015NewLine        int length = 3;Di2015NewLine        var potentialPath = message.Substring(idx, length);Di2015NewLine        var lastGoodPath = potentialPath;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        // Eat "\\" until we get an invalid pathDi2015NewLine        while (Directory.Exists(potentialPath)) {Di2015NewLine            lastGoodPath = potentialPath;Di2015NewLine            while (idx+length < message.Length && message[idx+length] != '\\\\')Di2015NewLine                length++;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            length++; // Include the trailing backslashDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            if (idx + length >= message.Length)Di2015NewLine                length = (message.Length - idx) - 1;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            potentialPath = message.Substring(idx, length);Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        potentialPath = message.Substring(idx);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        // Iterate over the files in directory we found until we get a matchDi2015NewLine        foreach (var file in Directory.EnumerateFiles(lastGoodPath)Di2015NewLine                                      .OrderByDescending(s => s.Length)) {Di2015NewLine            if (!potentialPath.StartsWith(file))Di2015NewLine                continue;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            // 'file' contains a valid file nameDi2015NewLine            break;Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

16066050Di2015UniqueSeparatorprivate static bool CanCopyAllFiles(string source, string dest)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    System.IO.FileInfo[] filesSource = new System.IO.DirectoryInfo(source).GetFiles();Di2015NewLine    System.IO.FileInfo[] filesTarget = new System.IO.DirectoryInfo(dest).GetFiles();Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    foreach (FileInfo fileInfo in filesSource)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        FileInfo tmp = filesTarget.FirstOrDefault(f => f.Name == fileInfo.Name);Di2015NewLine        if (tmp != null && tmp.LastWriteTime > fileInfo.LastWriteTime)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            return false;Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine    return true;Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

16073730Di2015UniqueSeparatorpublic string CalcCRC16(string strInput) {Di2015NewLine    ushort crc = 0xFFFF;Di2015NewLine    byte[] data = GetBytesFromHexString(strInput);Di2015NewLine    for (int i = 0; i < data.Length; i++) {Di2015NewLine        crc ^= (ushort)(data[i] << 8);Di2015NewLine        for (int j = 0; j < 8; j++) {Di2015NewLine            if ((crc & 0x8000) > 0)Di2015NewLine                crc = (ushort)((crc << 1) ^ 0x1021);Di2015NewLine            elseDi2015NewLine                crc <<= 1;Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine    return crc.ToString("X4");Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLinepublic Byte[] GetBytesFromHexString(string strInput) {Di2015NewLine    Byte[] bytArOutput = new Byte[] { };Di2015NewLine    if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(strInput) && strInput.Length % 2 == 0) {Di2015NewLine        SoapHexBinary hexBinary = null;Di2015NewLine        try {Di2015NewLine            hexBinary = SoapHexBinary.Parse(strInput);Di2015NewLine            if (hexBinary != null) {Di2015NewLine                bytArOutput = hexBinary.Value;Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine        catch (Exception ex) {Di2015NewLine            MessageBox.Show(ex.Message);Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine    return bytArOutput;Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

16085663Di2015UniqueSeparatorpublic static class XDocumentExtensionsDi2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    public static IEnumerable<string> SplitByLength(this XDocument source, string elementName, int maxLength)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        if (source == null)Di2015NewLine            throw new ArgumentNullException("source");Di2015NewLine        if (string.IsNullOrEmpty(elementName))Di2015NewLine            throw new ArgumentException("elementName cannot be null or empty.", "elementName");Di2015NewLine        if (maxLength <= 0)Di2015NewLine            throw new ArgumentException("maxLength has to be greater than 0.", "maxLength");Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        return SplitByLengthImpl(source, elementName, maxLength);Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    private static IEnumerable<string> SplitByLengthImpl(XDocument source, string elementName, int maxLength)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        var builder = new StringBuilder();Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        foreach (var element in source.Root.Elements(elementName))Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            var currentElementString = element.ToString();Di2015NewLine            if (builder.Length + currentElementString.Length > maxLength)Di2015NewLine            {Di2015NewLine                if (builder.Length > 0)Di2015NewLine                {Di2015NewLine                    yield return builder.ToString();Di2015NewLine                    builder.Clear();Di2015NewLine                }Di2015NewLine                elseDi2015NewLine                {Di2015NewLine                    throw new ArgumentException(Di2015NewLine                        "source document contains element with length greater than maxLength", "source");Di2015NewLine                }Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            builder.AppendLine(currentElementString);Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine        if (builder.Length > 0)Di2015NewLine            yield return builder.ToString();Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

16091580Di2015UniqueSeparatorstatic class ExtensionsDi2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    static string[] prefixes= { "f", "a", "p", "n", "Î¼", "m", string.Empty, "k", "M", "G", "T", "P", "E" };Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    public static string Nice(this double x, int significant_digits)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        //Check for special numbers and non-numbersDi2015NewLine        if(double.IsInfinity(x)||double.IsNaN(x)||x==0||significant_digits<=0)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            return x.ToString();Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine        // extract sign so we deal with positive numbers onlyDi2015NewLine        int sign=Math.Sign(x);Di2015NewLine        x=Math.Abs(x);Di2015NewLine        // get scientific exponent, 10^3, 10^6, ...Di2015NewLine        int sci= x==0? 0 : (int)Math.Floor(Math.Log(x, 10)/3)*3;Di2015NewLine        // scale number to exponent foundDi2015NewLine        x=x*Math.Pow(10, -sci);Di2015NewLine        // find number of digits to the left of the decimalDi2015NewLine        int dg= x==0? 0 : (int)Math.Floor(Math.Log(x, 10))+1;Di2015NewLine        // adjust decimals to displayDi2015NewLine        int decimals=Math.Min(significant_digits-dg, 15);Di2015NewLine        // format for the decimalsDi2015NewLine        string fmt=new string('0', decimals);Di2015NewLine        if(sci==0)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            //no exponentDi2015NewLine            return string.Format("{0}{1:0."+fmt+"}",Di2015NewLine                sign<0?"-":string.Empty,Di2015NewLine                Math.Round(x, decimals));Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine        // find index for prefix. every 3 of sci is a new indexDi2015NewLine        int index=sci/3+6;Di2015NewLine        if(index>=0&&index<prefixes.Length)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            // with prefixDi2015NewLine            return string.Format("{0}{1:0."+fmt+"}{2}",Di2015NewLine                sign<0?"-":string.Empty,Di2015NewLine                Math.Round(x, decimals),Di2015NewLine                prefixes[index]);Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine        // with 10^exp formatDi2015NewLine        return string.Format("{0}{1:0."+fmt+"}Â·10^{2}",Di2015NewLine            sign<0?"-":string.Empty,Di2015NewLine            Math.Round(x, decimals),Di2015NewLine            sci);Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    // test codeDi2015NewLine    static void Main(string[] args)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        double x=Math.PI/10e20;Di2015NewLine        doDi2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            Console.WriteLine(string.Format( "\\t{0,20} = {1}", x, x.Nice(4)));Di2015NewLine            x*=10;Di2015NewLine        } while(x<=Math.PI*10e20);Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

16091656Di2015UniqueSeparatorpublic static bool IsMatching(Color a, Color b, int percent)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    //this method is used to identify whether two pixels, Di2015NewLine    //of color a and b match, as in they can be consideredDi2015NewLine    //a solid color based on the acceptance value (percent)Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    int thresh = (int)(percent * 255);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    return Math.Abs(a.R - b.R) < thresh &&Di2015NewLine           Math.Abs(a.G - b.G) < thresh &&Di2015NewLine           Math.Abs(a.B - b.B) < thresh;Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine
16091656Di2015UniqueSeparator// assert: bitmap.Height > 2 && bitmap.Width > 2Di2015NewLineBitmapData data = bitmap.LockBits(new Rectangle(0, 0, bitmap.Width, bitmap.Height),Di2015NewLine                      ImageLockMode.ReadWrite, PixelFormat.Format24bppRgb);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLineint scaledPercent = percent * 255;Di2015NewLineunsafe {Di2015NewLine    byte *prevLine = (byte *)data.Scan0;Di2015NewLine    byte *currLine = prevLine + data.Stride;Di2015NewLine    byte *nextLine = currLine + data.Stride;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    for (int y=1; 16108293Di2015UniqueSeparatorprivate static unsafe void YUV2RGBManaged(byte[] YUVData, byte[] RGBData, int width, int height)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        //returned pixel format is 2yuv - i.e. luminance, y, is represented for every pixel and the u and v are alternatedDi2015NewLine        //like this (where Cb = u , Cr = y)Di2015NewLine        //Y0 Cb Y1 Cr Y2 Cb Y3 Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        /*http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms893078.aspxDi2015NewLine         * Di2015NewLine         * C = Y - 16Di2015NewLine         D = U - 128Di2015NewLine         E = V - 128Di2015NewLine         R = clip(( 298 * C           + 409 * E + 128) >> 8)Di2015NewLine         G = clip(( 298 * C - 100 * D - 208 * E + 128) >> 8)Di2015NewLine         B = clip(( 298 * C + 516 * D           + 128) >> 8)Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine         * here are a whole bunch more formats for doing this...Di2015NewLine         * http://stackoverflow.com/questions/3943779/converting-to-yuv-ycbcr-colour-space-many-versionsDi2015NewLine         */Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        fixed(byte* pRGBs = RGBData, pYUVs = YUVData)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            for (int r = 0; r < height; r++)Di2015NewLine            {Di2015NewLine                byte* pRGB = pRGBs + r * width * 3;Di2015NewLine                byte* pYUV = pYUVs + r * width * 2;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                //process two pixels at a timeDi2015NewLine                for (int c = 0; c < width; c += 2)Di2015NewLine                {Di2015NewLine                    int C1 = pYUV[1] - 16;Di2015NewLine                    int C2 = pYUV[3] - 16;Di2015NewLine                    int D = pYUV[2] - 128;Di2015NewLine                    int E = pYUV[0] - 128;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                    int R1 = (298 * C1 + 409 * E + 128) >> 8;Di2015NewLine                    int G1 = (298 * C1 - 100 * D - 208 * E + 128) >> 8;Di2015NewLine                    int B1 = (298 * C1 + 516 * D + 128) >> 8;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                    int R2 = (298 * C2 + 409 * E + 128) >> 8;Di2015NewLine                    int G2 = (298 * C2 - 100 * D - 208 * E + 128) >> 8;Di2015NewLine                    int B2 = (298 * C2 + 516 * D + 128) >> 8;Di2015NewLine#if trueDi2015NewLine                    //check for overflowDi2015NewLine                    //unsurprisingly this takes the bulk of the time.Di2015NewLine                    pRGB[0] = (byte)(R1 < 0 ? 0 : R1 > 255 ? 255 : R1);Di2015NewLine                    pRGB[1] = (byte)(G1 < 0 ? 0 : G1 > 255 ? 255 : G1);Di2015NewLine                    pRGB[2] = (byte)(B1 < 0 ? 0 : B1 > 255 ? 255 : B1);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                    pRGB[3] = (byte)(R2 < 0 ? 0 : R2 > 255 ? 255 : R2);Di2015NewLine                    pRGB[4] = (byte)(G2 < 0 ? 0 : G2 > 255 ? 255 : G2);Di2015NewLine                    pRGB[5] = (byte)(B2 < 0 ? 0 : B2 > 255 ? 255 : B2);Di2015NewLine#elseDi2015NewLine                    pRGB[0] = (byte)(R1);Di2015NewLine                    pRGB[1] = (byte)(G1);Di2015NewLine                    pRGB[2] = (byte)(B1);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                    pRGB[3] = (byte)(R2);Di2015NewLine                    pRGB[4] = (byte)(G2);Di2015NewLine                    pRGB[5] = (byte)(B2);Di2015NewLine#endifDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                    pRGB += 6;Di2015NewLine                    pYUV += 4;Di2015NewLine                }Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine
16108293Di2015UniqueSeparatorvoid YUV2RGB(void *yuvDataIn,void *rgbDataOut, int w, int h, int outNCh)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    const int ch2 = 2 * outNCh;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    unsigned char* pRGBs = (unsigned char*)rgbDataOut;Di2015NewLine    unsigned char* pYUVs = (unsigned char*)yuvDataIn;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    for (int r = 0; r < h; r++)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        unsigned char* pRGB = pRGBs + r * w * outNCh;Di2015NewLine        unsigned char* pYUV = pYUVs + r * w * 2;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        //process two pixels at a timeDi2015NewLine        for (int c = 0; c < w; c += 2)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            int C1 = pYUV[1] - 16;Di2015NewLine            int C2 = pYUV[3] - 16;Di2015NewLine            int D = pYUV[2] - 128;Di2015NewLine            int E = pYUV[0] - 128;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            int R1 = (298 * C1 + 409 * E + 128) >> 8;Di2015NewLine            int G1 = (298 * C1 - 100 * D - 208 * E + 128) >> 8;Di2015NewLine            int B1 = (298 * C1 + 516 * D + 128) >> 8;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            int R2 = (298 * C2 + 409 * E + 128) >> 8;Di2015NewLine            int G2 = (298 * C2 - 100 * D - 208 * E + 128) >> 8;Di2015NewLine            int B2 = (298 * C2 + 516 * D + 128) >> 8;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            //unsurprisingly this takes the bulk of the time.Di2015NewLine            pRGB[0] = (unsigned char)(R1 < 0 ? 0 : R1 > 255 ? 255 : R1);Di2015NewLine            pRGB[1] = (unsigned char)(G1 < 0 ? 0 : G1 > 255 ? 255 : G1);Di2015NewLine            pRGB[2] = (unsigned char)(B1 < 0 ? 0 : B1 > 255 ? 255 : B1);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            pRGB[3] = (unsigned char)(R2 < 0 ? 0 : R2 > 255 ? 255 : R2);Di2015NewLine            pRGB[4] = (unsigned char)(G2 < 0 ? 0 : G2 > 255 ? 255 : G2);Di2015NewLine            pRGB[5] = (unsigned char)(B2 < 0 ? 0 : B2 > 255 ? 255 : B2);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            pRGB += ch2;Di2015NewLine            pYUV += 4;Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

16108653Di2015UniqueSeparatorDirectoryInfo
16108653Di2015UniqueSeparatorDirectory.GetFiles(dirPath, "*.*", SearchOption.AllDirectories);Di2015NewLine
16108653Di2015UniqueSeparatorGetFiles
16108653Di2015UniqueSeparatorprivate void AddAllFilesOfAllSubdirsWithFilterToList(ref List<FileInfo> filesList, string dirPath, DateTime startDateUtc, DateTime? optionalEndDateUtc = null, List<string> blockedDirs = null)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    // Input validationDi2015NewLine    if (String.IsNullOrEmpty(dirPath))Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        throw new ArgumentException("Cannot search and empty path");Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    DirectoryInfo currentDir = new DirectoryInfo(dirPath);Di2015NewLine    if (!currentDir.Exists)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        throw new DirectoryNotFoundException(dirPath + " does not exist");Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine    if (filesList == null)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        filesList = new List<FileInfo>();Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    // Set endDate; add an hour to be safeDi2015NewLine    DateTime endDateUtc = optionalEndDateUtc ?? DateTime.UtcNow.AddHours(1);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    // The current folder's LastWriteTime DOES update every time a child FILE is written to,Di2015NewLine    // so if the current folder does not pass the date filter, we already know that no files within will pass, eitherDi2015NewLine    if (currentDir.LastWriteTimeUtc >= startDateUtc && currentDir.LastWriteTimeUtc <= endDateUtc)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        foreach (string filePath in Directory.GetFiles(dirPath, "*.*", SearchOption.TopDirectoryOnly))Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            FileInfo fileInfo = new FileInfo(filePath);Di2015NewLine            if (fileInfo.LastWriteTimeUtc > _sinceDate)Di2015NewLine            {Di2015NewLine                filesList.Add(fileInfo);Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    // Unfortunately, the current folder's LastWriteTime does NOT update every time a child FOLDER is written to,Di2015NewLine    // so we have to search ALL subdirectories regardless of the current folder's LastWriteTimeDi2015NewLine    foreach (string subDirPath in Directory.GetDirectories(dirPath))Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        if (blockedDirs == null || !blockedDirs.Any(p => subDirPath.ToLower().Contains(p)))Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            AddAllFilesOfAllSubdirsWithFilterToList(ref filesList, subDirPath, startDateUtc, optionalEndDateUtc, blockedDirs);Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

16112650Di2015UniqueSeparatorpublic static IEnumerable<T> Shuffle<T>(this IEnumerable<T> source, Random rng)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    T[] elements = source.ToArray();Di2015NewLine    for (int i = elements.Length - 1; i >= 0; i--)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        // Swap element "i" with a random earlier element it (or itself)Di2015NewLine        // ... except we don't really need to swap it fully, as we canDi2015NewLine        // return it immediately, and afterwards it's irrelevant.Di2015NewLine        int swapIndex = rng.Next(i + 1);Di2015NewLine        yield return elements[swapIndex];Di2015NewLine        elements[swapIndex] = elements[i];Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

16115248Di2015UniqueSeparatorstatic int SimpleBoyerMooreSearch(byte[] haystack, byte[] needle)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    int[] lookup = new int[256];Di2015NewLine    for (int i = 0; i < lookup.Length; i++) { lookup[i] = needle.Length; }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    for (int i = 0; i < needle.Length; i++)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        lookup[needle[i]] = needle.Length - i - 1;Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    int index = needle.Length - 1;Di2015NewLine    var lastByte = needle.Last();Di2015NewLine    while (index < haystack.Length)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        var checkByte = haystack[index];Di2015NewLine        if (haystack[index] == lastByte)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            bool found = true;Di2015NewLine            for (int j = needle.Length - 2; j >= 0; j--)Di2015NewLine            {Di2015NewLine                if (haystack[index - needle.Length + j + 1] != needle[j])Di2015NewLine                {Di2015NewLine                    found = false;Di2015NewLine                    break;Di2015NewLine                }Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            if (found)Di2015NewLine                return index - needle.Length + 1;Di2015NewLine            elseDi2015NewLine                index++;Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine        elseDi2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            index += lookup[checkByte];Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine    return -1;Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine
16115248Di2015UniqueSeparatorlbyte

16115248Di2015UniqueSeparatorIList
16115248Di2015UniqueSeparatorIList
16115248Di2015UniqueSeparator static int SimpleBoyerMooreSearch(IList<byte> haystack, IList<byte> needle)Di2015NewLine {Di2015NewLine    int[] lookup = new int[256];Di2015NewLine    for (int i = 0; i < lookup.Length; i++) { lookup[i] = needle.Count; }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    for (int i = 0; i < needle.Count; i++)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        lookup[needle[i]] = needle.Count - i - 1;Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    int index = needle.Count - 1;Di2015NewLine    var lastByte = needle[index];Di2015NewLine    while (index < haystack.Count)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        var checkByte = haystack[index];Di2015NewLine        if (haystack[index] == lastByte)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            bool found = true;Di2015NewLine            for (int j = needle.Count - 2; j >= 0; j--)Di2015NewLine            {Di2015NewLine                if (haystack[index - needle.Count + j + 1] != needle[j])Di2015NewLine                {Di2015NewLine                    found = false;Di2015NewLine                    break;Di2015NewLine                }Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            if (found)Di2015NewLine                return index - needle.Count + 1;Di2015NewLine            elseDi2015NewLine                index++;Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine        elseDi2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            index += lookup[checkByte];Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine    return -1;Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

16115310Di2015UniqueSeparator[DllImport("kernel32.dll")]Di2015NewLine[return: MarshalAs(UnmanagedType.Bool)]Di2015NewLinestatic extern bool GetProcessTimes(IntPtr hProcess, out System.Runtime.InteropServices.ComTypes.FILETIMEDi2015NewLine    lpCreationTime, out System.Runtime.InteropServices.ComTypes.FILETIME lpExitTime, out System.Runtime.InteropServices.ComTypes.FILETIME lpKernelTime,Di2015NewLine    out System.Runtime.InteropServices.ComTypes.FILETIME lpUserTime);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine[DllImport("kernel32.dll")]Di2015NewLine[return: MarshalAs(UnmanagedType.U4)]Di2015NewLinestatic extern UInt32 GetTickCount();Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLinestatic bool gbSetOldData = false;Di2015NewLinestatic UInt32 gmsOldTickCount = 0;Di2015NewLinestatic ulong gnsOldKernelTime = 0;Di2015NewLinestatic ulong gnsOldUserTime = 0;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLinepublic static double getCPUUsageForProcess(int nProcID = 0)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    //Get CPU usage for the process in with ID in 'nProcID'Di2015NewLine    //'nProcID' = process ID, or 0 for the current processDi2015NewLine    //RETURN:Di2015NewLine    //      = CPU usage: [0.0 - 1.0]Di2015NewLine    //      = Negative if errorDi2015NewLine    double fCPUUsage = -1.0;Di2015NewLine    tryDi2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        IntPtr hProcess = nProcID != 0 ? gameDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                    int numGuessesInt = -1;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                    while (numGuessesInt == -1)Di2015NewLine                    {Di2015NewLine                        /* Sets the number of guesses the user has to guess the word*/Di2015NewLine                        pickNumGuesses(ref numGuessesInt);Di2015NewLine = true;Di2015NewLine                            Console.WriteLine("You Win!  The word was " + word);Di2015NewLine                            /* Check if the user wants to play again.  If they do,Di2015NewLine                            * then solved is set to true, will end the loop,Di2015NewLine                            * otherwise, checkIfPlayAgain will close the program.*/Di2015NewLine                            checkIfPlayAgain();Di2015NewLine                        }Di2015NewLine                        else if (numGuessesInt <= 0)Di2015NewLine                        {Di2015NewLine                            solved = true;Di2015NewLine                            Console.WriteLine("You Lose! {Di2015NewLine                            /* If the user has not won or lost, call guessLetter,Di2015NewLine                            * display the word, minus guesses by 1*/Di2015NewLine }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    private static void initializeWordList()Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        words = new WordList();Di2015NewLine 16141922Di2015UniqueSeparatorpublic static bool IsAnagram(string s1, string s2)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    if (string.IsNullOrEmpty(s1) || string.IsNullOrEmpty(s2))Di2015NewLine        return false;Di2015NewLine    if (s1.Length != s2.Length)Di2015NewLine        return false;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    foreach (char c in s2)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        int ix = s1.IndexOf(c);Di2015NewLine        if (ix >= 0)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            s1 = s1.Remove(ix, 1);Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    return string.IsNullOrEmpty(s1);Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

Win32Exception(Marshal.GetLastWin32Error());Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        int processParametersOffset = Environment.Is64BitOperatingSystem ? 0x20 : 0x10;Di2015NewLine        tryDi2015NewLine 16151223Di2015UniqueSeparatorpublic static IEnumerable<string> GetScriptSection(string file, string section)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    var startMatch = string.Format("[{0}]", section);Di2015NewLine    var endMatch = string.Format("[/{0}]", section);Di2015NewLine    var lines = file.Split(Environment.NewLine.ToCharArray(), StringSplitOptions.RemoveEmptyEntries).Select(s => s.Trim()).ToList();Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    int startIndex = lines.FindIndex(f => f == startMatch) + 1;Di2015NewLine    int endIndex = lines.FindLastIndex(f => f == endMatch);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    if(endIndex == -1)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        endIndex = lines.FindIndex(startIndex,  f => f.StartsWith("[") && lines.IndexOf(f) > startIndex);Di2015NewLine        endIndex = endIndex == -1 ? lines.Count : endIndex;Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    return lines.GetRange(startIndex, endIndex - startIndex).Where(l => !string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(l)).ToList();Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

16171977Di2015UniqueSeparator    /// <summary>Di2015NewLine    /// Determines whether the host should buffer the <see cref="HttpResponseMessage"/> entity body.Di2015NewLine    /// </summary>Di2015NewLine    /// <param name="response">The <see cref="HttpResponseMessage"/>response for which to determineDi2015NewLine    /// whether host output buffering should be used for the response entity body.</param>Di2015NewLine    /// <returns><c>true</c> if buffering should be used; otherwise a streamed response should be used.</returns>Di2015NewLine    public virtual bool UseBufferedOutputStream(HttpResponseMessage response)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        if (response == null)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            throw Error.ArgumentNull("response");Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        // Any HttpContent that knows its length is presumably already buffered internally.Di2015NewLine        HttpContent content = response.Content;Di2015NewLine        if (content != null)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            long? contentLength = content.Headers.ContentLength;Di2015NewLine            if (contentLength.HasValue && contentLength.Value >= 0)Di2015NewLine            {Di2015NewLine                return false;Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            // Content length is null or -1 (meaning not known). 16191033Di2015UniqueSeparator/// <summary>A bounded blocking queue.</summary>Di2015NewLine/// <typeparam name="T">The element type of the queue, which must be a reference type.</typeparam>Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLinepublic sealed class BoundedBlockingQueue<T>: IDisposable where T: classDi2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    #region Construction and disposalDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    /// <summary>Constructor.</summary>Di2015NewLine    /// <param name="maxQueueSize">Di2015NewLine    /// The maximum size of the queue.Di2015NewLine    /// Calls to <see cref="Enqueue"/> when the queue is full will block until at least one item has been removed.Di2015NewLine    /// Calls to <see cref="Dequeue"/> when the queue is empty will block until a new item is enqueued.Di2015NewLine    /// </param>Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    public BoundedBlockingQueue(int maxQueueSize)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        if (maxQueueSize <= 0)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            throw new ArgumentOutOfRangeException("maxQueueSize");Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        _queue                  = new Queue<T>(maxQueueSize);Di2015NewLine        _itemsAvailable         = new Semaphore(0, maxQueueSize);Di2015NewLine        _spaceAvailable         = new Semaphore(maxQueueSize, maxQueueSize);Di2015NewLine        _queueStopped           = new ManualResetEvent(false);Di2015NewLine        _queueStoppedAndEmpty   = new ManualResetEvent(false);Di2015NewLine        _stoppedOrItemAvailable = new WaitHandle[] { _queueStopped, _itemsAvailable };Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    /// <summary>Disposal.</summary>Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    public void Dispose()Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        if (_itemsAvailable != null)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            _itemsAvailable.Close();Di2015NewLine            _spaceAvailable.Close();Di2015NewLine            _queueStopped.Close();Di2015NewLine            _queueStoppedAndEmpty.Close();Di2015NewLine            _itemsAvailable = null;          // Use _itemsAvailable as a flag to indicate that Dispose() has been called.Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    #endregion Construction and disposalDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    #region Public propertiesDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    /// <summary>The number of items currently in the queue.</summary>Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    public int CountDi2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        getDi2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            throwIfDisposed();Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            lock (_queue)Di2015NewLine <summary>Di2015NewLine    /// Signals that new items will no longer be placed into the queue.Di2015NewLine    /// After this is called, calls to <see cref="Dequeue"/> will return null immediately if the queue is empty.Di2015NewLine    /// Before this is called, calls to <see cref="Dequeue"/> will block if the queue is empty.Di2015NewLine    /// Attempting to enqueue items after this has been called will cause an exception to be thrown.Di2015NewLine    /// </summary>Di2015NewLine    /// <remarks>Di2015NewLine    /// If you use a different thread to enqueue items than the thread that calls Stop() you might get a race condition.Di2015NewLine    /// Di2015NewLine    /// If the queue is full and a thread calls Enqueue(), that thread will block until space becomes available in the queue.Di2015NewLine    /// If a different thread then calls Stop() while the other thread is blocked in Enqueue(), the item enqueued by the otherDi2015NewLine    /// thread may become lost since it will be enqueued after the special null value used to indiciate the end of theDi2015NewLine    /// stream is enqueued.Di2015NewLine    /// Di2015NewLine    /// To prevent this from happening, you must enqueue from the same thread that calls Stop(), or provide anotherDi2015NewLine    /// synchronisation mechanism to avoid this race condition.Di2015NewLine    /// </remarks>Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    public void Stop()Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        throwIfDisposed();Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        lock (_queue)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            _queueStopped.Set();Di2015NewLine            _stopped = true;Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    /// <summary>Di2015NewLine    /// Returns the front item of the queue without removing it, or null if the queue is currently empty.Di2015NewLine    /// A null return does NOT indicate that <see cref="Stop"/> has been called.Di2015NewLine    /// This never blocks.Di2015NewLine    /// </summary>Di2015NewLine    /// <returns>The front item of the queue, or null if the queue is empty.</returns>Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    public T Peek()Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        throwIfDisposed();Di2015NewLine        T result;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        lock (_queue)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            if (_queue.Count > 0)Di2015NewLine            {Di2015NewLine                result = _queue.Peek();Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLine            elseDi2015NewLine            {Di2015NewLine                result = null;Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        return result;Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    /// <summary>Di2015NewLine    /// Enqueues a new non-null item.Di2015NewLine    /// If there is no room in the queue, this will block until there is room.Di2015NewLine    /// An exception will be thrown if <see cref="Stop"/> has been called.Di2015NewLine    /// </summary>Di2015NewLine    /// <param name="item">The item to be enqueued. This may not be null.</param>Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    public void Enqueue(T item)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        throwIfDisposed();Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        if (item == null)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            throw new ArgumentNullException("item");Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        if (_stopped)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            throw new InvalidOperationException("Attempting to enqueue an item to a stopped queue.");Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        this.enqueue(item);Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    /// <summary>Di2015NewLine    /// Dequeues the next available item.Di2015NewLine    /// If <see cref="Stop"/> has been called, this returns null if the queue is empty.Di2015NewLine    /// Otherwise it blocks until an item becomes available (or <see cref="Stop"/> is called).Di2015NewLine    /// </summary>Di2015NewLine    /// <returns>The next available item, or null if the queue is empty and stopped.</returns>Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    public T Dequeue()Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        throwIfDisposed();Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        if (_isQueueStoppedAndEmpty)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            return null;Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        WaitHandle.WaitAny(_stoppedOrItemAvailable);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        lock (_queue)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            if (_stopped && (_queue.Count == 0))Di2015NewLine            {Di2015NewLine                _isQueueStoppedAndEmpty = true;Di2015NewLine                _queueStoppedAndEmpty.Set();Di2015NewLine                return null;Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLine            elseDi2015NewLine            {Di2015NewLine                T item = _queue.Dequeue();Di2015NewLine                _spaceAvailable.Release();Di2015NewLine                return item;Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    /// <summary>Waits forever for the queue to become empty AND stopped.</summary>Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    public void WaitUntilStoppedAndEmpty()Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        throwIfDisposed();Di2015NewLine        WaitUntilStoppedAndEmpty(Timeout.Infinite);Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    /// <summary>Waits up to the specified time for the queue to become empty AND stopped.</summary>Di2015NewLine    /// <param name="timeoutMilliseconds">The maximum wait time, in milliseconds.</param>Di2015NewLine    /// <returns>True if the wait succeeded, false if it timed-out.</returns>Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    public bool WaitUntilStoppedAndEmpty(int timeoutMilliseconds)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        throwIfDisposed();Di2015NewLine        return _queueStoppedAndEmpty.WaitOne(timeoutMilliseconds);Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    #endregion Public methodsDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    #region Private methodsDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    /// <summary>Enqueues a new item (which may be null to indicate the last item to go into the queue).</summary>Di2015NewLine    /// <param name="item">An item to enqueue.</param>Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    private void enqueue(T item)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        _spaceAvailable.WaitOne();Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        lock (_queue)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            _queue.Enqueue(item);Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        _itemsAvailable.Release();Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    ///       {Di2015NewLine            throw new ObjectDisposedException(this.GetType().FullName);Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    #endregion Private 16191033Di2015UniqueSeparator[TestMethod]Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLinepublic void TestBoundedBlockingQueue()Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    int maxQueueSize = 8;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    using (var queue = new BoundedBlockingQueue<string>(maxQueueSize))Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        // Fill the queue, but don't block.Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        for (int i = 0; i < maxQueueSize; ++i)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            int start1 = DateTimeFunctions.TickCount;Di2015NewLine            queue.Enqueue(i.ToString());Di2015NewLine            int elapsed1 = DateTimeFunctions.TickCount - start1;Di2015NewLine            Assert.IsTrue(elapsed1 < 100, "Took too long to enqueue an item.");  // Shouldn't have taken more than 100 ms to enqueue the item.Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        // Now if we try to enqueue something we should block (since the queue should be full).Di2015NewLine        // We can detect this by starting a thread that will dequeue something in a few secondsDi2015NewLine        // and then seeing how long the main thread took to enqueue something.Di2015NewLine        // It should have taken around the thread sleep time (+/- half a second or so).Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        int sleepTime = 2500;Di2015NewLine        int tolerance = 500;Di2015NewLine        Worker.Run(()=>{Thread.Sleep(sleepTime); queue.Dequeue();}, "TestBoundedBlockingQueue Dequeue()");Di2015NewLine        int start2 = DateTimeFunctions.TickCount;Di2015NewLine        queue.Enqueue(maxQueueSize.ToString());Di2015NewLine        int elapsed2 = DateTimeFunctions.TickCount - start2;Di2015NewLine        Assert.IsTrue(Math.Abs(elapsed2 - sleepTime) <= tolerance, "Didn't take the right time to enqueue an item.");Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        // Now verify that the remaining items in the queue are the expected ones,Di2015NewLine        // i.e. from "1".."maxQueueSize" (since the first item, "0", has been dequeued).Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        for (int i = 1; i <= maxQueueSize; ++i)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            Assert.AreEqual(i.ToString(), queue.Dequeue(), "Incorrect item dequeued.");Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        Assert.AreEqual(0, queue.Count);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        // Now if we try to dequeue something we should block (since the queue is empty).Di2015NewLine        // We can detect this by starting a thread that will enqueue something in 5 secondsDi2015NewLine        // and then seeing how long the main thread took to dequeue something.Di2015NewLine        // It should have taken around 5 seconds (+/- half a second or so).Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        string testValue = "TEST";Di2015NewLine        Worker.Run(()=>{Thread.Sleep(sleepTime); queue.Enqueue(testValue);}, "TestBoundedBlockingQueue Enqueue()");Di2015NewLine        start2 = DateTimeFunctions.TickCount;Di2015NewLine        Assert.AreEqual(testValue, queue.Dequeue(), "Incorrect item dequeued");Di2015NewLine        elapsed2 = DateTimeFunctions.TickCount - start2;Di2015NewLine        Assert.IsTrue(Math.Abs(elapsed2 - sleepTime) <= tolerance, "Didn't take the right time to enqueue an item.");Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine
